# .i18nignore — allowlist for scripts/scan-i18n.mjs
#
# Syntax:
#   literal         exact substring match
#   /regex/flags    regex (uses JS RegExp)
#   path/to/file    whole file ignored (no globs)
# Lines starting with # are comments. Blank lines ignored.

# ── Brand / proper nouns (design-spec §3-1) ─────────────────────────────────
>Testably<
>Jira<
>GitHub<
>Claude<
>Slack<
>Paddle<
>LemonSqueezy<
>Stripe<
>Supabase<
>Anthropic<

# ── Short data / unit fixtures that look like English ───────────────────────
>TCs<
>Note<
>Bug<
>Obs<
>Step<
# Single-letter weekday labels like >M<, >T<, >W< (Velocity sparkline)
/>[A-Z]</

# ── D-day / badge short forms (page.tsx getDDayBadge) ───────────────────────
>D-Day<
/>D[-+]\d+</

# ── HTTP / URL placeholders ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
/https:\/\/hooks\.slack\.com/
/teammate@company\.com/

# ── AC-9: Claude API responses in AIRunSummaryPanel (body text, not labels) ──
# The wrapper "Executive Summary"/"Failure Patterns" headers are i18n'd.
# Markdown/Jira/GitHub payload strings remain English by design (forwarded to
# external systems). Ignore the buildMarkdown / handleCreateJira / GitHub body
# templates specifically.
/\[AI Summary\]/
/\[Bug\] /
/\[Re-run\]/
/Root cause:/
/AI-detected failure cluster/
/Detected by Testably/
/## AI Run Summary/
/### Executive Summary/
/### Failure Patterns/
/### Recommendations/
/### Key Metrics/
/### Go\/No-Go/
/Generated by Testably/
# English-locked risk level + go/no-go enums returned from Claude
>HIGH RISK<
>MEDIUM RISK<
>LOW RISK<
>GO<
>NO-GO<

# ── Phase 2b run-detail: PDF export HTML cells (external output, locked EN) ──
# Dev Spec §4-5 / Design Spec §15-1. These strings live inside the
# handleExportPDF template literal and are forwarded to a printable window —
# translating them would break the exported report for external stakeholders.
#
# The scanner's JSX regex matches the short `>Word<` snippet, so we allowlist
# each PDF HTML label bare. These strings are ALSO used inside runs.* bundle
# values for the live UI (e.g. common.passed = 'Passed'), which is fine —
# bundle values are not scanned.
>AI Run Summary<
>Executive Summary<
>Key Metrics<
>Recommendations<
>Failure Patterns<
>Metric<
>Value<
>Total<
>Retest<
# Passed/Failed/Blocked/Untested also live inside the PDF stat-label cells
# (lines 601-605). They occur only inside the PDF template on run-detail —
# verified with grep. If future JSX usage appears elsewhere, scope the rule.
>Passed<
>Failed<
>Blocked<
>Untested<
# PDF table column headers (line 617-622)
>Test Case<
>Priority<
>Folder<
>Assignee<
>Status<
# Timer placeholder — digits-only format string (§4-5)
placeholder="00:00"
# em-dash separator rendered as text (TC list empty folder / assignee fallback)
>—<

# Phase 2b run-detail: showToast('type', t(...)) pattern — the scanner's
# showToast regex picks up the first string arg which in run-detail is the
# type marker 'error' / 'success' (5-7 char), not a translatable message.
# The actual message is already inside t(...).
showToast('error'
showToast('success'
showToast('info'
showToast('warning'
